==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opaline
<hw>O"pal*ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>opalin</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of, pertaining to, or like, opal in
appearance; having changeable colors like those of the opal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opaline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Opaline
<hw>O"pal*ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
opaline variety of yellow chalcedony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Opal glass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An opaline color or expanse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opalize</ent>⟦br⟧
